    <p> Now, let's explore some basic CSS selectors and properties:

<ul>

<li>Element Selector: Targets elements based on their tag name, e.g., h1, p, div.</li>
<li>Class Selector: Targets elements with a specific class attribute, e.g., .my-class.</li>
<li>ID Selector: Targets an element with a unique ID attribute, e.g., #my-id.</li>
<li>Color Property: Sets the text color, e.g., color: blue;.</li>
<li>Font Properties: Controls font styles like font-size, font-weight, and font-family.</li>
<li>Background Properties: Sets background colors or images, e.g., background-color: #f1f1f1;.</li>
<li>Margin and Padding Properties: Controls the spacing around and inside elements.</li>

</ul>
